  "body": "### Description\r\nFor the APIs under `/eth/v1/beacon/states/:stateId`, any request with `head` for the state ID returns a 404 when the head slot is empty.\r\n\r\nFor example run:\r\n`./build/install/teku/bin/teku --rest-api-enabled --data-storage-mode archive --Xinterop-enabled --network minimal`\r\n\r\nwait until a slot has passed (empty because there are no validators running) then run:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl --fail http://localhost:5051/eth/v1/beacon/states/head/fork\r\n```\r\n\r\nand it will fail with a 404 error. Whereas \r\n```\r\ncurl --fail http://localhost:5051/eth/v1/beacon/states/genesis/fork\r\n```\r\n\r\nworks.",
